9. Write code that prints Hello if 1 is stored in spam, prints Howdy if 2 is stored in spam, and prints Greetings! if anything else is stored in spam.



spam = int(input('Please input a number between 1 and 5 '))  # input function is used to request user contribution. User (string) contribution is stored in the spa variable as an integer 

if spam == 1:
    print('Hello')
elif spam == 2:
    print('Howdy')
else:
    print('Greetings!')
